            {"type": "paragraph", "content": "When you see a shape like `(3, 4)`, read it out loud as '3 rows and 4 columns'. When you see `(batch, features)`, think 'one row per example, one column per feature'. Naming the meaning of each dimension makes shape bugs easier to catch."},
